{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17608965","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17608965"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:39:08+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:39:08+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16057"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16057","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16057"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.55,0.28,0.17,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8748"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72418"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8748","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8748"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16057"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57888"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"1"},{"type":"tags","id":"23"},{"type":"tags","id":"44"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4422"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"9222"},{"type":"tags","id":"10330"},{"type":"tags","id":"10626"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20916"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20922"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72418","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/72418"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA woman in active labour requests information about available pain relief options.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is most commonly used for pain relief during the first stage of labour?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Transcutaneous electrical nerve stimulation","Nitrous oxide and oxygen mixture","Pudendal nerve block","Paracetamol alone","General anaesthesia"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EPain relief during labour can be achieved through various methods. \u003Cstrong\u003ETranscutaneous electrical nerve stimulation (TENS)\u003C/strong\u003E provides modest pain relief and is most effective when started early in labour, though evidence for its effectiveness is limited.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENitrous oxide and oxygen mixture\u003C/strong\u003E (typically 50:50) is commonly used during the first stage of labour as it is safe, self-administered, and provides rapid but short-acting pain relief.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPudendal nerve block\u003C/strong\u003E is typically reserved for the second stage of labour or for instrumental delivery. \u003Cstrong\u003EParacetamol alone\u003C/strong\u003E provides insufficient analgesia for labour pain. \u003Cstrong\u003EGeneral anaesthesia\u003C/strong\u003E is not used for labour pains and is typically reserved for emergency caesarean sections when regional anaesthesia is contraindicated.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOther options for labour pain management include:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENon-pharmacological: breathing techniques, positioning, water immersion\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPharmacological: epidural anaesthesia, opioids\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Multiple pharmacological and non-pharmacological options exist for labour pain management","Pain relief options range from simple positioning to regional anaesthesia","Different pain relief methods can be used at different stages of labour"],"references":["Rosen MA. Nitrous oxide for relief of labor pain: a systematic review. Am J Obstet Gynecol. 2002 May;186(5 Suppl Nature):S110-26. doi: 10.1067/mob.2002.121259. PMID: 12011877.","Broughton K, Clark AG, Ray AP. Nitrous Oxide for Labor Analgesia: What We Know to Date. Ochsner J. 2020 Winter;20(4):419-421. doi: 10.31486/toj.19.0102. PMID: 33408580; PMCID: PMC7755562.","Froessler B, Malek M, Jila M, Parange A, Kelly TL. The impact of withholding nitrous oxide in labour during the COVID-19 pandemic on maternal and neonatal outcomes. Aust N Z J Obstet Gynaecol. 2022 Dec;62(6):910-914. doi: 10.1111/ajo.13577. Epub 2022 Jul 4. PMID: 35781873; PMCID: PMC10083960.","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press.","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57888"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16057"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57888","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/57888"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-21T18:09:06+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-21T18:09:06+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8748"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72418"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"1","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/1"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude34","name":"Anaesthesia","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"5"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"23","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/23"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd30","name":"Obstetrics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"h